#i was getting batch effect based on which library the samples belonged to. This is aggravated by the fact that i have about 100 duplictaes (so 100 individual, but 200 samples). I cleaned the samples by selecting the 
# duplicate sample with higher variants called and run the pca again. it helped a bit but the PCA is still not explaining geentic variance but batch effect which is disappointing. Also I want to develop a better way
# to handle this duplicates, for example going from 2 samples to 1 but by adding the variants called ideally. Also there seems to be a very high correlation between variants called and maniculatus proportion...

